This article is a Presidential Memorandum from September 18, 2013, addressed to the Secretary of Defense. It discusses the approval of an agreement between the United States and Croatia regarding the exchange of atomic information within the context of NATO. The agreement, known as the ATOMAL Agreement, has been in force since March 12, 1965, with respect to the United States and other NATO members at that time. The memorandum states that the performance of the agreement, including the proposed cooperation and communication of Restricted Data with Croatia, will promote the common defense and security without posing an unreasonable risk. As a result, the memorandum approves the ATOMAL Agreement with Croatia and authorizes the Department of Defense to cooperate with Croatia in the context of NATO, subject to the requirements of the Atomic Energy Act of 1954. The memorandum is signed by President Barack Obama.